-- UBS Hires Citigroup’s David James as Joint Head of Broking
-- B y   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 2012-06-12T11:20:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-12/ubs-hires-citigroup-s-david-james-as-joint-head-of-broking-2-.html
UBS AG (UBSN) , Switzerland’s largest bank,
hired  David James  from Citigroup Inc. as joint head of corporate
broking with John Woolland in its U.K. team.  James starts in September at UBS, which acts as broker or
adviser to 34 FTSE 100 and 38 FTSE 250 clients, it said in a
memorandum to employees. The memo was confirmed by a spokesman
in London today.  James worked at Citigroup for the past 15 years including
nine years as head of corporate broking and as joint head of the
firm’s U.K. banking and broking business. His most recent role
was vice chairman of Europe, Middle East and Africa banking
since 2010.  Brokers in Britain liaise with investors on behalf of
companies, and often manage stock and bond offerings.  To contact the reporters on this story:
